{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HLYFxK7wAL75EjA9Ye8Jg7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The problem is clear. crdb-cluster-2 was updated to use TLS, but crdb-cluster-0 and crdb-cluster-1 are still running in insecure mode. This causes the TLS handshake failure:\n\n```\nW260701 09:27:36.231927 7767 gossip/client.go:121 ⋮ [T1,Vsystem,n2] 389  failed to start gossip client to ‹crdb-cluster-1.crdb-cluster.cockroachdb.svc.cluster.local:26257›: initial connection heartbeat failed: grpc: ‹connection error: desc = \"transport: authentication handshake failed: tls: first record does not look like a TLS handshake\"› [code 14/Unavailable]\n```\n\nThe rolling update is blocked because crdb-cluster-2 can't form quorum—it's trying to connect via TLS while the other pods remain in insecure mode, creating a mismatch that prevents the cluster from reaching consensus.\n\nThe fix requires a coordinated restart: scale down all pods simultaneously (or delete the StatefulSet), then scale back up so they all initialize in TLS mode together. The data persists in the PVCs, but there's a consideration around how CockroachDB handles the transition from insecure to TLS-encrypted storage.\n```\n\nActually, I realize the data itself isn't encrypted at rest in either mode—only the network traffic is encrypted in TLS mode. So the stored data should be compatible. The real requirement is that all three pods come up in TLS mode at the same time so they can form quorum with each other through TLS connections. Scaling to zero and back to three should accomplish this, since the PVCs preserve the data while all pods restart fresh in secure mode.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5328,"cache_read_input_tokens":37969,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5328},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c3ce2be6-5b8e-4bb8-978f-c7c755f9b167","uuid":"4064c14c-bc65-4dda-b711-fb5321c5e135","request_id":"req_011Ccb6kifPQcH5dVuWT38NQ"}
